#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:188
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kwallet; supports multiple wallets, so for the most secure operation, "
#| "you should use one wallet for local passwords, and another for network "
#| "passwords and form data. You can configure this behavior in the &kwallet; "
#| "&kcontrolcenter; module, however the default setting is to store "
#| "everything in one wallet."
msgid ""
"&kwallet5; supports multiple wallets, so for the most secure operation, you "
"should use one wallet for local passwords, and another for network passwords "
"and form data. You can configure this behavior in the &kwallet5; "
"&systemsettings; module, however the default setting is to store everything "
"in one wallet named <guilabel>kdewallet</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"&kwallet; understøtter at have flere tegnebøger, så den sikreste brug, bør "
"du bruge en tegnebog til lokale kodeord og en anden til netværkskodeord og "
"formulardata. Du kan indstille dette i &kwallet;s modul i kontrolcentret. "
"Imidlertid er standardindstillingen at gemme alt i en tegnebog."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:195
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "A wallet is by default closed, which means that you must supply a "
#| "password to open it. Once the wallet is opened, the contents can be "
#| "accessed."
msgid ""
"A wallet is by default closed, which means that you must supply a password "
"to open it. Once the wallet is opened, the contents can be read by any user "
"process, so this may be a security issue."
msgstr ""
"En tegnebog er normalt lukket, hvilket betyder at du skal sørge for et "
"kodeord for at åbne den. Når tegnebogen er åben, er der adgang til indholdet."

